  <discussion>Subspecies ocellatum is rather similar to subsp. humboldtii, but the yellowish sepals and petals with widely margined spots, lighter-colored pollen, and purplish bulb with notched scales are distinctive. In addition to the mainland, it occurs on the larger northern Channel Islands, where it is the only native lily (C. F. Smith 1976).</discussion>
